programme.title: Blood Origins Episode #13 – Jason Hairston "Mountain Soul"
programme.desc: There are those among us that purposefully seek out adventure. Purposefully seek out a test of mind, spirit, and body. That is Jason Hairston. You may know him as a leading force behind mountain hunting as the CEO and Founder of KUIU, but you may not know why he has dedicated his life, his livelihood, his brand to mountain hunting. To Jason, hunting brings him as close to the ultimate challenge as possible. An ethos of hunting that was buried in his DNA by his Dad, character traits formed as early child with a traditional bow, and now is being fulfilled in places where few humans dare to travel, and being perpetuated in how he is investing this love into his son.

programme.title: Blood Origins Episode #17 - Grant Woods "Press On"
programme.desc: You may recognize Grant Woods. He is one of the foremost advocates for whitetail deer management. However, his love for the outdoors, for restoration and management of habitats, his love of all things wildlife, not just deer, were seated into his DNA by his father. His dad buried within him morals and ethics about respecting wildlife, leaving a place better than you found it, and as such, Grant has raised his daughters and other with those same ethics. This episode is dedicated to Grant's Dad.

programme.title: Blood Origins Episode #18 - Jeremiah Doughty "Faith, Family, Food"
programme.desc: Faith. Family. Food. In that order. Jeremiah's story is seated in these three tenets. Raised a hunter, studied to become a minister, and then developed a debilitating allergy to bovine fat. In order to continue to feed red meat protein to his family, he had to revert to that which he knew was buried in his blood. He had to hunt to harvest his own meat. Process that meat and cook it. Though for Jeremiah this turned into a platform - a platform by which he could show and engage a much broader audience that wild game is delicious. It doesn't just have to be wrapped in bacon and smeared with cream cheese. There is so much more to it - and as such From Field to Plate was born.

programme.title: Blood Origins Episode #19 - Gerard Masih "Hunter"
programme.desc: Gerard Masih is a first generation Pakistani American. He is the epitome of someone who took up hunting as a result of the life that America as a country promised. Starting with a pellet gun he decided to follow that what was in his blood - bird hunting. Utilizing the public land system in California shaped his descent into becoming an avid waterfowler, and as they say, the rest is history. His two young sons are being raised as hunters, and his story represents the system in place of public lands, access, our 2nd amendment, and the ability to harvest your own food to feed your family

programme.title: Blood Origins Episode #20 - Louise Shockey "Perspectives"
programme.desc: Do you know why you hunt? If a non-hunter stopped you on the street and asked you the straight forward question about why you hunt what would you say? If that same non-hunter, opened up your social media feed, would they answer the SAME way? Our social media feeds and what we post is often a non-hunters only window into forming their perspective on what they believe hunting is, and hunters are. As hunters we have a duty to our community to portray ourselves appropriately. When you are the wife of one of the greatest icons of hunting the world has seen, then you would have a perspective completely unique.
